<TITLE> RMG workers demo for high pay </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 22 (bdnews24.com)  Workers of a readymade garment factory took to the streets Monday in the capital's Tejgaon area demanding pay hike. Hundreds of workers of Focus Fashion gathered at the Mohakhali-Satrasta crossing at around 9:30am, halting traffic on the road. Tejgaon zone deputy police commissioner Chowdhury Manjurul Kabir told bdnews24.com that the workers demonstrated to press for demands including pay hike and payment of overtime allowances. The situation is under control, he said. Efforts are being made to hold talks with workers, Kabir added. 
